    <section id="company">
      <h2>2. Company Overview</h2>
      <p><strong>Background and history:</strong> Established in 2000, the business has operated ~26 years as a roll-off dumpster rental provider in the Orlando, FL market, serving construction, renovation, and property clean-out demand. Its customer base is referral-driven — 95% of new clients arrive via referral and 99% of business is repeat.</p>
      <p><strong>Ownership structure:</strong> Not disclosed in the blind listing; legal entity name withheld. Likely a single-owner LLC or S-corp given the SDE-based presentation. Confirm via FL Division of Corporations (Sunbiz) once the legal name is released under NDA.</p>
      <p><strong>Key milestones:</strong> 2000 — founded in Orlando. (Undated) — fleet built to ~186 dumpsters + multiple roll-off trucks; modern dispatch software adopted, reducing owner load. 2026 — listed for sale at $849,000 via Biz Depot Brokers.</p>
      <p><strong>Org structure &amp; leadership:</strong> Lean. Owner in a "largely managerial" role; experienced drivers handle field operations; dispatch software coordinates routing. No GM/COO layer — the owner is the de facto manager, a transition consideration even though daily field work does not depend on the owner.</p>
    </section>

